narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Study scores of great classical works. Argue about them. Thengenuflecting, hand-wringingseek to emulate them.
If you haven't taken a class with Friedmann yet, you're doing the music major wrong. This class is a fantastic analysis of everything Mozart/Beethoven/Haydn.

I would recommend it for students with considerable background in performance or composition. This course will allow to expand greatly the knowledge of the classical repertory, as well as deepen the understanding of classical forms and rhetoric.
This course is brilliant, but requires a great deal of work. Far more difficult if one does not perform classical instrumental literature
